+## 211 Service Partner Pilot Readiness
+
+WALLET-210 staging pilots should use a synthetic wallet and one named partner
+DID before any live client data is invited. The pilot is ready to demonstrate
+only when every step below is visible through the 211-AI UI or public wallet API
+and backed by `ipfs_datasets_py.wallet` audit events:
+
+1. Create or load a wallet, then add one encrypted document through the Uploads
+   screen or `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/documents/text`.
+2. Add one encrypted location record through the Uploads location form or
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations`. UI lists and audit evidence must use
+   record IDs, storage status, and coarse/proof outputs; do not display precise
+   coordinates after capture.
+3. Register an approved analytics template with consent copy, allowed fields,
+   k-threshold, epsilon budget, retention mapping, and reviewer role recorded in
+   the target signoff evidence.
+4. Share partner access with `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/records/{record_id}/grants`.
+   Use a partner DID, a named purpose such as `211_service_partner_pilot`,
+   explicit `record/analyze` ability, bounded output types, and an expiration
+   for staged runs.
+5. Have the partner open the recipient-access UI and run only the allowed
+   derived output. The receipt should show active status and a share proof code;
+   the audit timeline should include `grant/create`, `invocation/issue` when
+   user presence is required, `invocation/verify`, and the derived action.
+6. Create a location-region proof from Proof Center or
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations/{location_record_id}/region-proofs`.
+   Public inputs may include `claim`, `region_id`, and policy hash values, but
+   must not include latitude, longitude, target coordinates, witnesses, raw
+   address text, or credential values.
+7. Use the analytics screen or
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/analytics/contributions` to contribute only
+   consented derived/coarse fields, then run the approved aggregate endpoint.
+   Sparse-cell suppression, budget accounting, and contribution nullifiers must
+   remain enforced.
+8. Revoke the partner grant from the recipient-access UI or
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/grants/{grant_id}/revoke`, then verify the same
+   partner grant can no longer analyze, decrypt, prove, match, or export.
+9. Open the Audit screen and confirm the wallet timeline includes document and
+   location `record/add`, partner `grant/create`, derived partner action,
+   `proof/create`, `analytics/consent_create`, `analytics/contribute`, and
+   `grant/revoke` without plaintext, precise coordinates, proof witnesses, or
+   secret values.
+
+The regression test for this pilot is
+`wallet_interface/ui/tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts`. It starts a live wallet
+API with durable local staging storage, drives the UI for document upload,
+location capture, proof creation, analytics consent/contribution, grant
+revocation, and audit review, and uses API calls for the partner grant and
+aggregate count.
+
